    • addConnectionRequestProxyListener

      public void addConnectionRequestProxyListener(ConnectRequestProxyListener listener)
      Adds the given ConnectRequestProxyListener to the extension hook, to be later notified of CONNECT requests received by the local proxy.

      By default, the ConnectRequestProxyListeners added are removed from the local proxy when the extension is unloaded.

      Parameters:
      listener - the ConnectRequestProxyListener that will be added and then notified
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the given listener is null.
      Since:
      2.5.0

    • addOverrideMessageProxyListener

      public void addOverrideMessageProxyListener(OverrideMessageProxyListener overrideMessageProxyListener)
      Adds the given overrideMessageProxyListener to the extension hook, to be later added to the Proxy.

      By default, the OverrideMessageProxyListeners added to this extension hook are removed from the Proxy when the extension is unloaded.

      Parameters:
      overrideMessageProxyListener - the OverrideMessageProxyListener that will be added to the Proxy
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the given overrideMessageProxyListener is null.
      Since:
      2.7.0

    • getOverrideMessageProxyListenerList

      public List<OverrideMessageProxyListener> getOverrideMessageProxyListenerList()
      Gets the OverrideMessageProxyListeners added to this hook.

      While it's possible to add the listener with this method it's not recommended, use addOverrideMessageProxyListener(OverrideMessageProxyListener) whenever possible. The accessibility of this method might change in a future version (to package access).

      Returns:
      a List containing the added OverrideMessageProxyListeners, never null.
      Since:
      2.3.0

    • addContextDataFactory

      public void addContextDataFactory(ContextDataFactory contextDataFactory)
      Adds the given ContextDataFactory to the extension hook, to be later added to the Model.

      By default, the ContextDataFactorys added are removed from the Model when the extension is unloaded.

      Parameters:
      contextDataFactory - the ContextDataFactory that will be added to the Model
      Since:
      2.5.0

    • addApiImplementor

      public void addApiImplementor(ApiImplementor apiImplementor)
      Adds the given apiImplementor to the extension hook, to be later added to the API.

      By default, the ApiImplementors added to this extension hook are removed from the API when the extension is unloaded.

      Parameters:
      apiImplementor - the ApiImplementor that will be added to the ZAP API
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the given apiImplementor is null.
      Since:
      2.6.0
